owl:Class.dc:description: A Cargo is some Thing that is not a Person and is occupying a Vehicle during transit.
An occupant is a Person who is occupying a Vehicle during transit. An Occupant may be a Driver or a Passenger
A Schedule is a plan for some Activity to occur at/over some point in time.
Added for organizational purposes, to identify all classes included in the Urban System ontology.
